-- Coca-Cola to buy Glaceau for $4.1 billion
-- 
-- Fri May 25, 2007 6:50am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/25/us-glaceau-coke-idUSN2542986420070525

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Coca-Cola Co. ( KO.N ) on Friday said it would acquire vitamin water maker Glaceau for $4.1 billion in cash. 

 Glaceau, also known as Energy Brands Inc., is 30 percent owned by India's Tata Tea Ltd. TTTE.BO and is the No. 2 maker of enhanced water behind PepsiCo Inc.'s ( PEP.N ) Propel. Coca-Cola said the deal would add to its earnings per share in the first full year after the agreement is completed.